<item>
            <title>[JDK-8299570] [JVMCI] Insufficient error handling when CodeBuffer is exhausted</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8299570</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>This is a follow-up from &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8298720&quot; title=&quot;Insufficient error handling when CodeBuffer is exhausted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8298720&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8298720&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
When CodeBuffer::expand fails, MacroAssembler::emit_trampoline_stub fails on Aarch64. The following call chain does not handle this properly:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
CodeInstaller::site_Call -&amp;gt; CodeInstaller::pd_relocate_JavaMethod -&amp;gt; NativeCall::trampoline_jump -&amp;gt; MacroAssembler::emit_trampoline_stub&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Similar, CompiledStaticCall::emit_to_interp_stub can fail as well and needs to be handled in CodeInstaller::site_Call.</description>
